definitions.definition: A style of multi-act theatrical entertainment which originated from France and flourished in Europe and North America from the 1880s through the 1920s.

main_definition: ( historical , uncountable ) A style of multi-act theatrical entertainment which originated from France and flourished in Europe and North America from the 1880s through the 1920s.
secondary_definitions: ( historical , countable ) An entertainment in this style.
